The corporate world has a main goal which is to maximize profits. In order to accomplish this, companies have spent decades learning how to best market products, sell services, and generate interest in the hopes of making money. As companies have grown, they are able to put more investment into researching how to use appearances to generate more profit. As such, professionals at most companies use psychology and evolutionary biology to manipulate consumers into using and purchasing their products and services.\n
